1
00:02:06,626 --> 00:02:07,544
Han Se-gye!

2
00:02:27,272 --> 00:02:29,899
AUNTIE

3
00:02:34,737 --> 00:02:36,072
Are you really...

4
00:02:40,368 --> 00:02:41,327
I'm sorry.

5
00:02:47,542 --> 00:02:50,003
My face...

6
00:03:13,193 --> 00:03:16,946
My face is not coming back.

7
00:04:03,117 --> 00:04:05,328
"EPISODE 13"

8
00:04:07,956 --> 00:04:09,249
How can you be so OK?

9
00:04:09,332 --> 00:04:11,334
Did you think I would die?

10
00:04:12,377 --> 00:04:15,630
I controlled the car

11
00:04:15,713 --> 00:04:18,258
just right, so...

12
00:04:18,341 --> 00:04:20,885
So you laid down in a coma?

13
00:04:20,969 --> 00:04:24,264
Wouldn't it be weird to lay down
if you're awake?

14
00:04:26,182 --> 00:04:28,893
I went to the gates of heaven.

15
00:04:29,435 --> 00:04:31,104
When I tried to enter,

16
00:04:31,271 --> 00:04:33,022
they said to bring you, too,
so I came back.

17
00:04:33,106 --> 00:04:34,357
Why are you killing me now?

18
00:04:35,441 --> 00:04:36,818
It wouldn't work.

19
00:04:37,318 --> 00:04:42,198
You don't want to sacrifice.
You can't be a priest. Give up.

20
00:04:44,033 --> 00:04:46,953
Actually, I've been thinking
about that, too.

21
00:04:47,912 --> 00:04:49,956
-Really?
-I'm not sure.

22
00:04:50,039 --> 00:04:51,874
Let me know when you are sure.

23
00:04:54,877 --> 00:04:55,878
Lift the bowl.

24
00:05:04,721 --> 00:05:06,222
Thank you for the food. I'll go.

25
00:05:06,306 --> 00:05:07,140
Go where?

26
00:05:09,225 --> 00:05:10,226
To find Se-gye.

27
00:05:11,311 --> 00:05:14,230
She must've gotten
pointlessly lost somewhere.

28
00:05:15,773 --> 00:05:17,775
Mom, I'm going now.

29
00:05:18,192 --> 00:05:19,360
Thank you for the food.

30
00:05:19,444 --> 00:05:23,031
Did you just drink your meal
without chewing it?

31
00:05:24,991 --> 00:05:27,618
I'll make a bone soup,
so bring Se-gye too.

32
00:05:27,702 --> 00:05:30,121
Why... why bone soup again?

33
00:05:31,289 --> 00:05:34,751
Bone soup is the best for strengthening
bones and giving stamina.

34
00:05:34,834 --> 00:05:37,045
That's what you are serving all month!

35
00:05:37,128 --> 00:05:38,629
How old are you?

36
00:05:38,713 --> 00:05:40,298
You still complain about food.

37
00:05:41,049 --> 00:05:43,801
Then, I will come back with Se-gye.

38
00:05:43,885 --> 00:05:45,345
-Come together.
-OK.

39
00:05:45,428 --> 00:05:46,721
You!

40
00:05:47,430 --> 00:05:48,431
Your son is the best!

41
00:05:49,015 --> 00:05:50,433
-Bye.
-Bye!

42
00:05:50,516 --> 00:05:52,435
Call me.

43
00:05:54,312 --> 00:05:55,563
Can you reach Se-gye?

44
00:05:56,356 --> 00:05:57,774
Do you feel OK?

45
00:05:59,192 --> 00:06:01,110
I came here by myself. I'm fine.

46
00:06:01,903 --> 00:06:03,279
Can you reach her?

47
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:05,490
You can, right?

48
00:06:06,574 --> 00:06:09,786
If Se-gye wanted to hide
because she is sorry--

49
00:06:09,869 --> 00:06:11,079
She came over.

50
00:06:12,497 --> 00:06:13,915
But she disappeared.

51
00:06:13,998 --> 00:06:16,417
When? Where?

52
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:18,127
You should've held her.

53
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:20,755
What was her face like

54
00:06:22,590 --> 00:06:23,716
when you saw her last time?

55
00:06:25,426 --> 00:06:26,469
An old man.

56
00:06:27,970 --> 00:06:28,971
She was an old man.

57
00:06:29,639 --> 00:06:30,848
Even after a week...

58
00:06:32,475 --> 00:06:35,311
Han se-gye looked the same.

59
00:06:38,856 --> 00:06:40,608
She said her face was not coming back.

60
00:06:44,112 --> 00:06:45,071
So?

61
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:49,325
For a long time, I've been thinking

62
00:06:50,368 --> 00:06:52,412
something like this might happen.

63
00:06:54,163 --> 00:06:56,040
So what are you going to do?

64
00:06:57,375 --> 00:06:58,584
If Se-gye is like that forever,

65
00:07:00,795 --> 00:07:03,214
if she has to live as an old man forever,

66
00:07:04,841 --> 00:07:06,217
can you still love her?

67
00:07:14,350 --> 00:07:15,351
I'm not sure.

68
00:07:16,936 --> 00:07:20,440
Will I be able to love her forever?

69
00:07:22,191 --> 00:07:24,569
Can I not care what other people think?

70
00:07:25,695 --> 00:07:27,738
Can I not judge myself?

71
00:07:29,657 --> 00:07:31,659
Can I spend a whole life with her?

72
00:07:37,415 --> 00:07:39,000
Please help me.

73
00:07:45,548 --> 00:07:46,382
You're the best!

74
00:08:02,356 --> 00:08:04,942
I tried really hard to conclude on my own,

75
00:08:05,443 --> 00:08:06,360
but I couldn't.

76
00:08:20,041 --> 00:08:20,875
All these people...

77
00:08:22,293 --> 00:08:25,755
Why are they all marked as Han Se-gye?

78
00:08:28,549 --> 00:08:31,052
NEITHER SHE NOR HER SITUATION MAKES SENSE.

79
00:08:34,805 --> 00:08:36,724
You just lost your chance.

80
00:08:43,898 --> 00:08:45,942
The chance to be honest with someone.

81
00:08:46,025 --> 00:08:47,235
I know well

82
00:08:48,027 --> 00:08:50,488
that those chances don't come often.

83
00:08:52,823 --> 00:08:54,659
It means they are all Han Se-gye.

84
00:09:07,296 --> 00:09:09,298
He's really crazy in love.

85
00:09:15,638 --> 00:09:16,847
HAN SE-GYE

86
00:09:16,931 --> 00:09:18,641
HAN SE-GYE

87
00:09:18,766 --> 00:09:22,436
HAN SE-GYE

88
00:09:24,313 --> 00:09:26,315
She is his whole life.

89
00:09:29,819 --> 00:09:31,237
I didn't need to worry.

90
00:09:32,154 --> 00:09:33,906
Why was I worried?

91
00:09:40,705 --> 00:09:44,041
I thought a day like this might come
one day.

92
00:09:51,048 --> 00:09:56,512
Although I didn't know
I would look like this.

93
00:10:07,273 --> 00:10:08,399
I miss him.

94
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:13,237
Even when I look like this,
I still miss him.

95
00:10:15,323 --> 00:10:17,116
I'm dying to see him.

96
00:10:33,090 --> 00:10:34,467
I'm getting off.

97
00:11:22,348 --> 00:11:23,891
After becoming like this,

98
00:11:25,726 --> 00:11:28,562
I thought I had to send you away.

99
00:11:29,689 --> 00:11:31,399
I kept thinking that.

100
00:11:32,316 --> 00:11:34,235
But I couldn't.

101
00:11:36,153 --> 00:11:36,987
So,

102
00:11:38,072 --> 00:11:39,907
I wanted to talk.

103
00:11:41,242 --> 00:11:42,827
I wanted to beg.

104
00:11:45,413 --> 00:11:47,540
I won't ask for anything.

105
00:11:47,915 --> 00:11:52,086
I will just come to see you sometimes.

106
00:11:53,671 --> 00:11:57,633
If you live like that, what will I do?

107
00:12:01,345 --> 00:12:03,264
Do you know how much I suffered?

108
00:12:05,474 --> 00:12:07,476
Because I was afraid
of how people would think of me,

109
00:12:08,477 --> 00:12:10,730
I almost lost you.

110
00:12:12,064 --> 00:12:13,023
After realizing that,

111
00:12:14,817 --> 00:12:16,277
I began to hate myself again.

112
00:12:17,820 --> 00:12:18,779
While I dated you,

113
00:12:20,364 --> 00:12:21,782
while I loved you,

114
00:12:22,408 --> 00:12:25,077
and while I was loved by you,
I forgot things.

115
00:12:26,871 --> 00:12:28,164
But they came back.

116
00:12:29,415 --> 00:12:33,419
I almost lived that awful life again.

117
00:12:34,253 --> 00:12:35,546
Seo Do-jae!

118
00:12:38,799 --> 00:12:40,718
I'm ready to give up everything.

119
00:12:41,677 --> 00:12:43,512
I can leave my family and work.

120
00:12:44,972 --> 00:12:48,309
I'm ready to go to you.

121
00:12:49,351 --> 00:12:51,604
That's how I'll live.

122
00:12:54,732 --> 00:12:55,608
I am fine,

123
00:12:57,610 --> 00:12:59,236
no matter how you look.

124
00:13:35,648 --> 00:13:36,899
How is it possible?

125
00:13:38,692 --> 00:13:40,569
How can you live like that?

126
00:14:00,047 --> 00:14:01,423
I'm me, right?

127
00:14:03,467 --> 00:14:05,177
I came back!

128
00:14:34,540 --> 00:14:36,542
You crazy...

129
00:14:38,502 --> 00:14:41,130
That's what I want to say.
Were you crazy?

130
00:14:41,547 --> 00:14:42,631
You said I should trust you.

131
00:14:42,756 --> 00:14:44,258
And that's what you did?

132
00:14:44,675 --> 00:14:47,052
-How could you crash your car?
-What?

133
00:14:48,095 --> 00:14:50,556
I wanted to hitÂ Chae Yu-ri, but I didn't.
Why?

134
00:14:51,015 --> 00:14:52,600
You are really crazy!

135
00:14:56,312 --> 00:14:59,899
Why didn't your face come back?

136
00:15:00,232 --> 00:15:01,400
I don't know.

137
00:15:02,359 --> 00:15:03,360
It just didn't come back.

138
00:15:04,028 --> 00:15:05,237
How did you come back?

139
00:15:05,613 --> 00:15:07,156
I don't know that either.

140
00:15:08,073 --> 00:15:09,199
Suddenly...

141
00:15:10,409 --> 00:15:12,119
Has it ever made sense?

142
00:15:13,913 --> 00:15:15,706
Your disease needs to be consistent!

143
00:15:16,457 --> 00:15:17,750
Whatever.

144
00:15:18,459 --> 00:15:21,837
When you didn't come back, I was afraid
my business would go bankrupt.

145
00:15:23,464 --> 00:15:24,673
Am I just money to you?

146
00:15:27,051 --> 00:15:27,927
Of course.

147
00:15:30,179 --> 00:15:33,098
When you go next time,
leave Gging-ggang here.

148
00:15:34,266 --> 00:15:37,186
She suffered so much that
she got skinny!

149
00:15:37,269 --> 00:15:39,772
What do you mean skinny?
I fed her really well.

150
00:15:40,439 --> 00:15:41,607
You just fed yourself.

151
00:15:41,690 --> 00:15:43,734
I even got snacks for her!

152
00:15:43,817 --> 00:15:44,944
Only your face got chubby.

153
00:15:46,654 --> 00:15:48,238
I heard Han Se-gye got plastic surgery.

154
00:15:48,530 --> 00:15:51,617
Something went wrong,
and that's why she's not on TV.

155
00:15:51,700 --> 00:15:52,701
Isn't she pregnant?

156
00:15:53,285 --> 00:15:55,454
Someone I know saw her in the hospital.

157
00:15:55,537 --> 00:15:56,664
No way.

158
00:15:56,747 --> 00:15:59,416
Her agent president was in the hospital.
Maybe she was mistaken.

159
00:15:59,917 --> 00:16:00,918
Watch what you say.

160
00:16:01,001 --> 00:16:04,088
If you say the wrong thing these days,
you get sued.

161
00:16:04,672 --> 00:16:07,174
See? It's a strange situation to anyone.

162
00:16:08,342 --> 00:16:10,970
I just need to give a little hint.

163
00:16:17,851 --> 00:16:19,395
Hi, Reporter Park.

164
00:16:20,104 --> 00:16:23,399
I have an interesting story
about Han Se-gye.

165
00:16:36,453 --> 00:16:39,581
She asks for a week off every month
in any contract.

166
00:16:40,499 --> 00:16:42,334
Or she runs away.

167
00:16:42,418 --> 00:16:43,877
Why does she need to run away?

168
00:16:45,254 --> 00:16:48,340
Off days are too regular to think
she just doesn't want to work.

169
00:16:49,591 --> 00:16:50,718
Look at this!

170
00:16:51,427 --> 00:16:52,761
Isn't this strange?

171
00:16:52,845 --> 00:16:54,972
She didn't go in, but she came out.

172
00:16:57,266 --> 00:17:00,102
Where did you get this?

173
00:17:01,395 --> 00:17:04,314
I don't know.
Maybe my coordinator gave it to me?

174
00:17:04,857 --> 00:17:06,191
Or my manager?

175
00:17:06,567 --> 00:17:07,735
Anyway, someone gave it to me.

176
00:17:09,111 --> 00:17:11,613
What do you think it is?
I don't know.

177
00:17:12,156 --> 00:17:13,824
She's doing this again!

178
00:17:13,907 --> 00:17:15,784
Oh, hi Se-gye.

179
00:17:16,744 --> 00:17:18,912
-Han Se-gye.
-There she is.

180
00:17:20,998 --> 00:17:23,167
What's this?
Did you call her to come here?

181
00:17:24,585 --> 00:17:26,837
Maybe she's under a lot of stress.

182
00:17:27,254 --> 00:17:30,049
She keeps saying I change my face.

183
00:17:32,801 --> 00:17:34,053
She watched too many cartoons.

184
00:17:38,265 --> 00:17:39,641
That's not it.

185
00:17:40,184 --> 00:17:42,644
I have a proof right here.

186
00:17:43,020 --> 00:17:44,938
-If you look at this...
-Then what?

187
00:17:46,398 --> 00:17:48,901
What's there? I only see myself.

188
00:17:51,153 --> 00:17:52,654
You went out of the bathroom, but...

189
00:17:52,738 --> 00:17:57,534
You need to see a doctor.
An inferiority complex is a disease, too.

190
00:17:57,951 --> 00:17:59,453
Whose loss do you think that'll be?

191
00:18:00,496 --> 00:18:03,582
Don't be dumb.
Try to see the real situation.

192
00:18:04,666 --> 00:18:07,127
Even if you get away like this,

193
00:18:07,211 --> 00:18:08,087
as long as I know--

194
00:18:08,170 --> 00:18:09,797
I think you forgot.

195
00:18:20,182 --> 00:18:23,227
What? Did you think I'd be gracious?

196
00:18:23,769 --> 00:18:25,145
You're the one who said

197
00:18:25,729 --> 00:18:28,273
I don't show up at work,
I run away fromÂ the shooting scene,

198
00:18:28,357 --> 00:18:29,733
and I meet any man.

199
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:31,902
That's all about me, not you.

200
00:18:34,863 --> 00:18:35,781
So this is me!

201
00:18:37,074 --> 00:18:38,909
-Hey!
-What?

202
00:18:40,994 --> 00:18:42,746
Do you want to pour one, too?

203
00:18:44,248 --> 00:18:45,916
In the middle of this crowd?

204
00:18:47,543 --> 00:18:48,627
Will you be able to do it?

205
00:18:54,675 --> 00:18:55,926
I'm used to it.

206
00:18:56,718 --> 00:18:59,429
Pouring a drink won't change
how people see me.

207
00:19:00,639 --> 00:19:03,016
People will talk about me
for a couple of weeks, at most.

208
00:19:03,433 --> 00:19:06,395
My reputation is bad already.
I don't care.

209
00:19:08,355 --> 00:19:09,273
One more thing.

210
00:19:14,361 --> 00:19:15,821
I'm warning you.

211
00:19:18,115 --> 00:19:19,283
Stop talking crazy.

212
00:19:21,243 --> 00:19:22,619
Do I change my face?

213
00:19:24,621 --> 00:19:25,956
I wish I could.

214
00:19:31,503 --> 00:19:33,213
So that I can kill you
with a different face.

215
00:19:36,508 --> 00:19:39,052
Then no one will know.

216
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:42,389
You'll die. I'll vanish.

217
00:19:44,516 --> 00:19:47,102
That would be the perfect crime.

218
00:19:55,235 --> 00:19:57,571
Why? Are you a bit scared now?

219
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:02,284
I'll go now.

220
