00:42:43,519 --> 00:42:47,147
He probably wants something
that's worth the risk.

544
00:42:47,481 --> 00:42:49,149
What couldn't to be OK, though?

545
00:42:49,608 --> 00:42:51,485
It better be OK!

546
00:42:51,777 --> 00:42:54,530
I'm really, really not going to
let it happen, OK?

547
00:42:54,947 --> 00:42:58,117
I'm gonna show what the Strategic
Planning Department is all about!

548
00:43:00,369 --> 00:43:02,121
Are... are you crying now?

549
00:43:02,454 --> 00:43:03,872
-No
-Yes, you are.

550
00:43:03,956 --> 00:43:05,124
I said no.

551
00:43:05,207 --> 00:43:06,083
Boss, here...

552
00:43:06,709 --> 00:43:08,502
I'm not crying...

553
00:43:09,837 --> 00:43:10,796
It's OK.

554
00:43:16,010 --> 00:43:17,595
Wait for me!

555
00:43:20,306 --> 00:43:21,974
You've gone through difficult times.

556
00:43:22,683 --> 00:43:23,809
It wasn't that bad.

557
00:43:24,435 --> 00:43:26,979
Right.
I am the one who had difficult times.

558
00:43:29,064 --> 00:43:31,025
Well, that's true.

559
00:43:31,567 --> 00:43:32,401
You did well.

560
00:43:34,236 --> 00:43:36,196
Could you not use the past tense?

561
00:43:36,363 --> 00:43:37,698
More difficulties are awaiting.

562
00:43:38,115 --> 00:43:40,951
Sorry for making more work for you.

563
00:43:42,161 --> 00:43:45,205
It's fine.
It's an investment for the future.

564
00:43:45,748 --> 00:43:47,916
I have to make you the President
so that I can be a CEO.

565
00:43:50,669 --> 00:43:53,130
I'll take good care of it,
so that it doesn't become an issue.

566
00:43:53,756 --> 00:43:55,424
I'm a genius. I can do this.

567
00:43:55,966 --> 00:43:57,635
Do you still have the dream?

568
00:43:57,718 --> 00:43:59,928
It is not a dream. It's a realistic goal.

569
00:44:01,430 --> 00:44:04,683
By now, this issue will start
to leak outside.

570
00:44:05,434 --> 00:44:07,478
-What's next?
-Next is...

571
00:44:10,397 --> 00:44:11,273
to wait.

572
00:44:14,818 --> 00:44:17,821
What? Prosopagnosia?

573
00:44:18,113 --> 00:44:18,947
Yes.

574
00:44:19,031 --> 00:44:21,784
I heard he told
his employees about it today. In person!

575
00:44:24,328 --> 00:44:25,954
Is that a serious disease?

576
00:44:27,206 --> 00:44:29,875
I don't recognize
people that well, either.

577
00:44:30,417 --> 00:44:33,337
So, what's it like?

578
00:44:33,962 --> 00:44:35,714
He can't see or what?

579
00:44:35,964 --> 00:44:37,174
Can you explain it simply?

580
00:44:37,257 --> 00:44:40,761
Even if he sees a face,
he cannot tell who the person is.

581
00:44:41,011 --> 00:44:41,887
What?

582
00:44:44,348 --> 00:44:46,642
OK. Symptoms are not important.

583
00:44:47,142 --> 00:44:49,603
The fact that he has
the disease is important.

584
00:44:49,687 --> 00:44:52,648
How can we let an ill person take charge
of the company, right?

585
00:44:52,731 --> 00:44:55,109
That's not right.
It'll cause a big issue.

586
00:44:56,777 --> 00:45:00,406
This was what Cho Gi-ho was talking about.

587
00:45:00,489 --> 00:45:02,199
DASHI TOUR PRESIDENT CHOI GI-HO

588
00:45:06,787 --> 00:45:08,038
T-ROAD CEO KIM

589
00:45:12,543 --> 00:45:14,712
President Choi, did you hear the news?

590
00:45:14,795 --> 00:45:15,713
Hear what?

591
00:45:15,838 --> 00:45:16,714
Just that...

592
00:45:16,797 --> 00:45:20,384
our Director Seo has a sad story.

593
00:45:22,094 --> 00:45:23,887
I felt so bad for him.

594
00:45:24,596 --> 00:45:27,141
-He has... what's it called?
-Prosopagnosia.

595
00:45:27,224 --> 00:45:28,976
Prosopagnosia?

596
00:45:29,059 --> 00:45:29,977
Is that right?

597
00:45:30,227 --> 00:45:35,023
He revealed the hidden card you prepared.

598
00:45:35,107 --> 00:45:38,777
He is not an average man.

599
00:45:38,902 --> 00:45:40,529
Did he reveal that himself?

600
00:45:40,612 --> 00:45:42,239
He did!

601
00:45:43,157 --> 00:45:46,118
Oh my. You must be disappointed.

602
00:45:48,036 --> 00:45:52,040
It would've worked better if you had
shared it with me in the firstÂ place.

603
00:45:52,124 --> 00:45:55,043
Business is all about cooperation.

604
00:45:59,465 --> 00:46:00,424
Turn the car around.

605
00:46:01,467 --> 00:46:02,593
Turn it around!

606
00:46:06,513 --> 00:46:08,557
-You can't go in.
-Don't you dare!

607
00:46:16,648 --> 00:46:18,066
It's OK. You can leave.

608
00:46:24,907 --> 00:46:26,450
Can't you knock?

609
00:46:26,784 --> 00:46:28,494
You just revealed the card like that?

610
00:46:29,036 --> 00:46:30,120
Are you insane?

611
00:46:33,832 --> 00:46:34,833
You said it was a present.

612
00:46:37,544 --> 00:46:39,338
I get to decide where to unwrap it.

613
00:46:42,007 --> 00:46:42,925
Or was it a bomb?

614
00:46:44,426 --> 00:46:46,512
Then, I threw it at you.

615
00:46:47,012 --> 00:46:48,597
-Kang Sa-ra!
-I...

616
00:46:50,599 --> 00:46:51,850
won't marry you.

617
00:46:54,561 --> 00:46:56,063
You are out of your mind.

618
00:46:56,563 --> 00:46:58,899
I helped you out of sympathy
and now, you do this to me?

619
00:46:59,483 --> 00:47:02,069
-You don't know what's scary.
-I do know.

620
00:47:03,779 --> 00:47:05,489
I was almost on your side.

621
00:47:08,617 --> 00:47:09,993
That's what's really scary.

622
00:47:10,619 --> 00:47:12,621
Stop playing around.

623
00:47:13,121 --> 00:47:15,123
I went easy on you as you are a woman,
and...

624
00:47:17,167 --> 00:47:18,752
-Who are you?
-Delivery service.

625
00:47:20,963 --> 00:47:23,298
Who's this scum? What are you two?

626
00:47:23,382 --> 00:47:25,759
I called him.
I have a delivery to send out.

627
00:47:27,719 --> 00:47:30,222
I was suspicious,
and it seems I was right.

628
00:47:30,305 --> 00:47:32,933
Are you making all this fuss
because of a guy?

629
00:47:33,016 --> 00:47:34,810
Kang Sa-ra, really?

630
00:47:35,143 --> 00:47:37,521
Do you really think I did this
because of a guy?

631
00:47:37,855 --> 00:47:40,691
This involves a lot of guys.

632
00:47:52,911 --> 00:47:53,745
Are you alright?

633
00:47:56,123 --> 00:47:57,165
No, I'm not.

634
00:48:01,962 --> 00:48:04,464
I wanted to show you what I've given up.

635
00:48:06,258 --> 00:48:07,676
That's why I asked you to come.

636
00:48:09,469 --> 00:48:10,345
I want to...

637
00:48:14,349 --> 00:48:15,809
give up something, too.

638
00:48:17,311 --> 00:48:18,145
Then do it.

639
00:48:30,741 --> 00:48:33,660
Dashi Tour President Choi,
what brings you here?

640
00:48:33,744 --> 00:48:36,538
You must be her brother.
You are both out of your minds.

641
00:48:38,665 --> 00:48:40,167
You are still impolite.

642
00:48:40,250 --> 00:48:42,794
You must've heard.
Your sister won't marry me.

643
00:48:44,254 --> 00:48:46,548
-So, I want to break the contract.
-Go ahead.

644
00:48:50,761 --> 00:48:53,347
Maybe you don't see what's going on.

645
00:48:54,681 --> 00:48:55,807
You have a disease.

646
00:48:57,142 --> 00:48:59,227
Don't you know
how disadvantageous it could be?

647
00:48:59,311 --> 00:49:00,562
How would I know?

648
00:49:03,440 --> 00:49:05,651
PENDING APPROVAL
STRATEGIC PLANNING DEPARTMENT

649
00:49:05,734 --> 00:49:07,110
AGREEMENT WITH DASHI TOUR

650
00:49:08,987 --> 00:49:09,905
Is this it?

651
00:49:11,490 --> 00:49:13,909
Hey, take it.

652
00:49:15,786 --> 00:49:16,745
Break the contract.

653
00:49:20,332 --> 00:49:22,709
I've been playing with you,
but I am not one to trifle with.

654
00:49:23,669 --> 00:49:25,796
What? Played?

655
00:49:25,879 --> 00:49:28,215
Why do you think I went easy on you?

656
00:49:29,007 --> 00:49:30,384
Because you were helpful?

657
00:49:30,968 --> 00:49:32,344
Because you were scary?

658
00:49:33,387 --> 00:49:34,304
No.

659
00:49:34,846 --> 00:49:36,515
The only reason was

660
00:49:37,349 --> 00:49:38,350
because of my sister.

661
00:49:40,185 --> 00:49:42,312
Now that my sister has removed
you from her life,

662
00:49:42,854 --> 00:49:46,358
I have no reason to put up with you.

663
00:49:53,407 --> 00:49:54,950
So what are you trying to do now?

664
00:49:55,867 --> 00:49:58,370
Trash needs to be treated like trash.

665
00:50:01,623 --> 00:50:02,958
You, you...

666
00:50:04,084 --> 00:50:05,002
Don't you dare hit me.

667
00:50:05,460 --> 00:50:08,588
Do you think I'll just hit you?

668
00:50:10,298 --> 00:50:11,174
Hey!

669
00:50:11,550 --> 00:50:16,805
Why do you think I have an aquarium
big enough to fit a person?

670
00:50:31,945 --> 00:50:32,946
Get out of here.

671
00:50:33,655 --> 00:50:34,906
Don't come near her, again.

672
00:50:35,407 --> 00:50:37,325
If you show up in front of my sister,

673
00:50:39,077 --> 00:50:40,037
you'll be dead.

674
00:50:41,288 --> 00:50:42,330
Not only you,

675
00:50:43,373 --> 00:50:45,959
but your company will die, too.

676
00:50:49,796 --> 00:50:52,507
Ju-hwan, the guest is leaving.

677
00:50:59,264 --> 00:51:02,476
Why would you want to do
an autograph event now?

678
00:51:02,559 --> 00:51:03,685
I told you not to do it.

679
00:51:04,478 --> 00:51:06,271
It is a good time to work.

680
00:51:07,064 --> 00:51:09,232
Showing my face like this is even better.

681
00:51:10,150 --> 00:51:13,528
My fans feel assured
when they see my face in person.

682
00:51:14,529 --> 00:51:17,783
That's because you trained them
so well for many years.

683
00:51:19,951 --> 00:51:20,952
She's Han Se-gye!

684
00:51:21,036 --> 00:51:22,537
You're so pretty!

685
00:51:22,662 --> 00:51:23,955
-Gosh!
-It's Han Se-gye!

686
00:51:27,459 --> 00:51:28,794
HAN SE-GYE AUTOGRAPH EVENT

687
00:51:33,882 --> 00:51:36,551
You're so pretty! Thank you!

688
00:51:38,595 --> 00:51:41,973
-I'm a fan! Thank you!
-Thank you.

689
00:51:42,766 --> 00:51:43,934
Thank you!

690
00:51:46,686 --> 00:51:49,356
Do you see my eyes?

691
00:51:49,439 --> 00:51:51,191
What about them? Do they hurt?

692
00:51:53,360 --> 00:51:56,154
You make me work overnight.
My company doesn't even do that to me.

693
00:51:57,280 --> 00:51:58,448
I got red eyes.

694
00:51:59,574 --> 00:52:01,535
Please, stop causing trouble.

695
00:52:01,868 --> 00:52:03,912
I stay up all night,
writing comments online.

696
00:52:04,830 --> 00:52:07,415
Sorry. There's nothing I can say.

697
00:52:08,625 --> 00:52:11,169
But this guy is worthÂ fighting for.

698
00:52:12,045 --> 00:52:12,879
He is a chaebol!

699
00:52:14,214 --> 00:52:18,468
If we get sued for fighting for you,
wouldn't he pay for the lawsuit?

700
00:52:19,344 --> 00:52:22,472
If that happens, call my agency.
I will pay.

701
00:52:23,723 --> 00:52:24,641
Gosh.

702
00:52:25,475 --> 00:52:28,937
If you hadn't been such a good actress,
I could've stopped being your fan.

703
00:52:29,020 --> 00:52:30,939
You've been saying that for ten years now.

704
00:52:31,731 --> 00:52:32,566
I know.

705
00:52:34,609 --> 00:52:36,278
By the way, are you busy after this?

706
00:52:36,361 --> 00:52:37,904
No, not really. Why?

707
00:52:39,197 --> 00:52:40,407
If you're not busy,

708
00:52:41,616 --> 00:52:42,868
marry me.

709
00:52:44,953 --> 00:52:46,580
You've been saying that
for ten years, too.

710
00:52:47,539 --> 00:52:49,457
-Marry me.
-When I have more time.

711
00:52:56,131 --> 00:52:58,258
I'm so lucky.

712
00:52:59,634 --> 00:53:01,928
I'm loved for no reason.

713
00:53:03,305 --> 00:53:04,806
I'm so lucky.

714
00:53:05,849 --> 00:53:08,643
I'm loved by someone
who's loved for no reason.

715
00:53:11,021 --> 00:53:12,355
What about you?

716
00:53:13,398 --> 00:53:15,150
Was there anything special
about your day?

717
00:53:15,609 --> 00:53:16,443
Well...

718
00:53:17,903 --> 00:53:19,154
I did some cleaning up.

719
00:53:19,446 --> 00:53:20,989
Wow, good job!

720
00:53:22,282 --> 00:53:23,742
You cleaned up on your own!

721
00:53:34,294 --> 00:53:35,962
I'm curious about something.

722
00:53:39,174 --> 00:53:40,300
About your disease,

723
00:53:42,552 --> 00:53:44,888
may I ask how it happened?

724
00:53:46,806 --> 00:53:49,017
I thought it might hurt you too much
to ask,

725
00:53:51,770 --> 00:53:53,230
so I couldn't.

726
00:54:00,153 --> 00:54:01,863
My father was a sculptor.

727
00:54:03,949 --> 00:54:07,118
He was born free-spirited.

728
00:54:08,745 --> 00:54:10,664
While he was married to my mom,

729
00:54:11,623 --> 00:54:13,416
he left for Europe by himself.

730
00:54:14,125 --> 00:54:17,420
He left my mother and me behind.

731
00:54:19,798 --> 00:54:22,008
But he was still my father.

732
00:54:24,177 --> 00:54:26,930
We were family,
but we were no better than strangers.

733
00:54:28,348 --> 00:54:30,934
And I heard
my father was in critical condition.

734
00:54:32,644 --> 00:54:36,398
He said he wanted to see me
before he died.

735
00:54:55,458 --> 00:54:56,543
I arrived.

736
00:54:57,210 --> 00:54:58,878
I'm just leaving the hotel.

737
00:54:59,629 --> 00:55:01,172
I'm on my way to the hospital.

738
00:55:01,298 --> 00:55:02,882
I'll be there as soon as I'm done here.

739
00:55:03,550 --> 00:55:05,552
-Sorry.
-I'll go first and wait for you.

740
00:55:06,428 --> 00:55:08,763
Come before it's too late.

741
00:56:38,645 --> 00:56:40,063
Faster. This way!

742
00:57:37,495 --> 00:57:38,329
Do-jae!

743
00:57:47,088 --> 00:57:47,922
Do-jae.

744
00:57:51,843 --> 00:57:52,969
Do-jae!

745
00:59:27,146 --> 00:59:28,273
My son,

746
00:59:29,899 --> 00:59:31,651
hurry and wake up.

747
00:59:35,863 --> 00:59:37,574
You have to wake up...

748
00:59:39,659 --> 00:59:41,160
and see your father.

749
01:00:29,125 --> 01:00:30,209
Do-jae!

750
01:00:32,795 --> 01:00:36,549
Who... are you?

751
01:00:49,145 --> 01:00:50,563
That was ten years ago.

752
01:01:05,078 --> 01:01:05,912
I...

753
01:01:08,665 --> 01:01:10,166
I have to go home.

754
01:01:11,334 --> 01:01:12,168
Now?

755
01:01:18,675 --> 01:01:20,426
I have something to do.

756
01:01:24,263 --> 01:01:25,181
Sorry.

757
01:01:26,307 --> 01:01:28,226
-I'll take you home.
-No.

758
01:01:29,477 --> 01:01:30,311
It's OK.

759
01:01:32,522 --> 01:01:35,733
-Then, I'll walk you to the door.
-It's OK. I'll go alone.

760
01:01:36,567 --> 01:01:37,610
I can go alone.

761
01:01:38,611 --> 01:01:39,904
Is this something urgent?

762
01:01:42,031 --> 01:01:42,865
Yes.

763
01:01:43,449 --> 01:01:44,450
I forgot about...

764
01:01:46,577 --> 01:01:47,662
an urgent thing...

765
01:01:51,124 --> 01:01:52,458
I forgot.

766
01:01:55,795 --> 01:01:58,798
This is the bad thing
about having a successful girlfriend.

767
01:02:01,551 --> 01:02:02,510
Go home safely.

768
01:02:02,927 --> 01:02:04,345
Call me when you arrive.

769
01:02:38,880 --> 01:02:39,714
You!

770
01:02:41,632 --> 01:02:43,760
You don't recognize faces, do you?

771
01:02:44,093 --> 01:02:46,387
How much can you recognize?
Do you recognize your family?

772
01:02:49,015 --> 01:02:49,974
May I help you?

773
01:02:50,057 --> 01:02:51,642
Am I not better than her?

774
01:02:53,394 --> 01:02:55,730
Oh, can you not tell the difference?

775
01:02:56,355 --> 01:02:58,149
You don't know how I feel, do you?

776
01:02:59,108 --> 01:03:02,862
Fine. You don't even remember me.

777
01:03:09,660 --> 01:03:11,162
I practiced while watching them.

778
01:03:11,746 --> 01:03:13,289
Practice for recognizing different people.

779
01:03:14,040 --> 01:03:15,166
It didn't work.

780
01:03:15,875 --> 01:03:18,169
I haven't loved myself since that day.

781
01:03:18,920 --> 01:03:19,754
Not even once.

782
01:03:22,340 --> 01:03:23,758
How can I say that

783
01:03:24,383 --> 01:03:26,135
when I'm such a mess?

784
01:03:26,552 --> 01:03:27,678
It's not OK for me.

785
01:03:28,429 --> 01:03:32,225
I want to see you.

786
01:03:34,352 --> 01:03:35,978
I just want to recognize you.

787
01:03:39,565 --> 01:03:40,858
What will I do?

788
01:03:43,653 --> 01:03:45,655
I'm so sorry. What should I do?

789
01:04:12,598 --> 01:04:14,600
I don't deserve to be with him.

790
01:04:15,142 --> 01:04:18,479
How dare I smile? How dare I be happy?

791
01:04:19,105 --> 01:04:20,940
I don't deserve any of that!

792
01:05:12,867 --> 01:05:16,120
FROM: UNCLE

793
01:05:25,129 --> 01:05:26,547
Did you get home safely?

794
01:05:30,259 --> 01:05:32,261
I should've taken you home.

795
01:05:34,055 --> 01:05:36,182
I keep regretting
that I let you leave like that.

796
01:05:45,524 --> 01:05:46,442
Han Se-gye?

797
01:05:48,235 --> 01:05:51,322
Seo Do-jae, listen carefully.

798
01:05:56,452 --> 01:05:58,663
I am the reason for your disease.

799
01:06:00,414 --> 01:06:01,582
What do you mean?

800
01:06:03,209 --> 01:06:05,461
It's my fault that it happened to you.

801
01:06:37,660 --> 01:06:40,913
It's my fault
that you have to live like this.

802
01:06:40,997 --> 01:06:44,250
Saving your life was
the best thing I've ever done.

803
01:06:44,333 --> 01:06:47,503
I didn't know who else I should call,
so I called you.

804
01:06:47,586 --> 01:06:48,796
I feel less lonely now.

805
01:06:48,879 --> 01:06:51,465
This woman cannot live without me.

806
01:06:52,008 --> 01:06:55,678
We can't be happy together.

807
01:06:55,803 --> 01:06:58,472
